The paper deals with the design and analysis of a new signaling method over a bandlimited channel with additive white Gaussian noise, which is a common problem in information theory and communication systems (cs.IT). The method involves intensity modulation and direct detection, which are also relevant topics in communication systems (cs.COMM). The channel is modeled as a bandlimited channel with nonnegative input, which is a physical constraint that is often considered in communication systems (cs.PHY). The paper also discusses the use of Nyquist and root-Nyquist pulses, which are commonly used in digital signal processing and communication systems (cs.DS). Finally, the paper investigates the trade-off between power and bandwidth, which is a fundamental problem in networked systems and communication networks (cs.NI).
